      "rationale": "Blood viscosity (Carreau-Yasuda model coefficients), inlet flow rate, and rotational speed are the primary inputs. Nominal values sourced from FDA protocol; uncertainty ranges assigned from published measurement uncertainty data. Monte Carlo UQ propagated these three inputs through 500 simulation samples. Note: ranking of which input contributes most to NIH variance is not yet established — sensitivity analysis is planned for a future study phase but has not been executed."
